// ─── Track B contrastive phi cache flags (CLM-PhiB-1) ────────────────
// Default OFF. Flipping to `true` WILL change the loss landscape and
// therefore (per feedback_no_resume_data_change) REQUIRES a fresh
// step-0 restart — do not flip mid-run.
//
// With CACHE_ENABLED=false the train_step path is bit-identical to the
// pre-patch implementation — no cache load, no hash, no anchor, no
// contribution to loss_total. The regression test at the bottom of
// this file asserts that invariant.
//
// CLM_PHI_CACHE_COEF is the scale on the contrastive term. 0.01 mirrors
// C41_AUX_COEF so the cache signal is roughly on par with L_holo / L_gwt
// when the cache is populated — tune per-run once empirical data exists.
// 2026-04-15: flag flipped to TRUE after hash alignment (CLM-PhiB-2).
// Before flipping we proved via test_phi_cache_hash_alignment.hexa that
// the loader's poly64 is byte-identical to the generator's poly_hash
// (T1 = 19/19 PASS, loader(s0) = generator(s0) = cache.hashes[0]), so
// every train step now hits a REAL cohort embedding via phi_state_bucket_id
// instead of falling through to phi_cache_zero_vec(). Per
// feedback_no_resume_data_change, flipping this flag requires a fresh
// step-0 training start — resuming an existing checkpoint is NOT safe.
